  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Weight Loss after surgery</measure>
    <time_frame>Preop, Postop, Six Months, and Annually</time_frame>
    <description>Baseline weight is recorded preoperatively. Time points after surgery when weight is recorded are two weeks, six weeks, 6 months, 1 year, 18 months, 2 years, then annually on the anniversary date of surgery.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Resolution of Co-morbidities, such as Type 2 Diabetes, Sleep Apnea, Hypertension</measure>
    <time_frame>Preop, Postop, Six Months, Annually</time_frame>
    <description>Preoperatively co-morbidities of morbid obesity are recorded as well as treatment (ie: medications, CPAP machine). Resolution of co-morbidities postoperatively is measured/recorded for example by blood tests, sleep study, as well as changes or discontinuation of medications &amp;/or interventions.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
